{"questionId":"22001969","questionHtml":"<p>Given that the area of the logo is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>area of logo = area of rectangle – area of segments&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>area of one segment&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35672</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn></math>&nbsp;(do not accept an answer in degrees)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award (<em><strong>M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> if there is more than one solution.<br>Award (<em><strong>M1)(A1FT)A0</strong></em> if the candidate works in degrees and obtains a&nbsp;final answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>135</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>030</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22001969","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ1.3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that the area of the logo is 13.4 cm2, find the value of θ.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.8—Solving trig equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}